data.title: Ali Selim
data.text:
Biography

Ali Selim was born on July 1, 1990 in Göteborg and made his IFK Göteborg debut in the 2008 season, which was also the debut season of team mate Robin Söder. Selim was part of IFK Göteborg's youth program before making his debute with the first team, and is as a result of that regarded by the club as a home-grown player. At 17 years, 10 months and 0 days, on May 1, 2008, he took part his first competetive game against Skövde AIK in a Svenska cupen game that ended 2–1. He has spent one season with the IFK Göteborgs first team, and during his career he played in 1 first team game. In the 2008 season he had a part in IFK Göteborg winning the Swedish Cup. 34 year old Selim completed his last season with IFK Göteborg 2008.
